\ntwo and four-door types. Pontiac\nwill start with txvo-door sedans.\nFord showed three lines, the\nFord, Mercury and Lincoln, when\nit first went into production. But\nth\u00ab Lincoln is far away as yet.\nThe company was canceled on its\nlank engine and then reinstated\nThe tang engine is made in the\nLincoln plant and until the con\ntract is completed, there is litllr\nrhanre of Lincolns being made\nthere.\nChevrolet xx ill probably siick to\nsedans at t its! although the busi\nness coupe xxas a big seller in its\nprewar days. Plymouth wdll xer>\nlikely do the same.\n0\nQuinn Heads Dodge\nC. Quinn has been\nnamed sales manager of Dodge.\nHe has been assistant sales man*\nager since 1944.\nQuinn started with Dodge In\n19.T5 in the retail end. In 1935,\nhe joined the division as coast\nmerchandising representative\nand advanced to district man- j\nager for southern California and\nArizona He joined the home\noffice staff in 1^44.\n\nMore Price Delay\nFord has delayed its public\nshowing of 194 A models at deal*\ners' show rooms because of labor\ni roubles holding up romponents.\nThis means that prices will not\nbe announced either, as ex\npected. the latter pari of ihe\nmonth.\nIt. may force the hand< of\nsome of the Ford rix'als. xxhn\nhad been planning to hold back\ntheir prices until Ford set the\npace. If their cars are ready\nfor market before the public\nshowing of Fords, they will\nhave to make their own puce\nlags,\n94\nStation Wagons Next\nAnd don't he surprised if right\nbehind the sedans, you find\u2014of\nall things\u2014stat'on wagons being\nproduced. As least one company\nhas an eye on the station wagon\nmarket and will rush them into\nproduction.\nThe reason for this Is that the\nbodies are made of wood, not\nsteel, and therefore can he had\nright now. Then there is quite a\nnumber of buyers who are sta\ntion wagon minded and eager to\nget one,\n\nBuick Returns Bush\nRuick ha\u00ab reassigned J R.\nRush ax Pacific regional man\nager in charge of all Went\nCoast state*. Hts headquarter*\nwill he in San Francisco.\nRush left u similar post In\n1942 to handle special liaison\nwork between Buick plants and\nthe army air forces. He main\ntained olTicps in Dayton to\nfacilitate procurement of Lib\neiator bomber and cargo plane\nengines, manufactured by Pmck\nfor the AAF,\nAd Firm Addst\nI to Staff\nRoss Roy, Inc, today announced\nthe apjiointnient of Kenneth C\nLovgren, Ralph E. Davis, Lloyd\nJones and Robert L. Garrison to\nLovgren has served as senior\ncopy writer for Chicago advertis\ning acencies. including Young A\nRuhicam. Inc.. MarFarland, Ave\nyarri A Co. and Henri, Hurst A\nMcDonald.\nDaus started his Detroit art\nand advertising career in 1922 and\nduring the Inst three scars was\nassociate editor of \u201cProduction\nEngineering and Management.\u2019\u2019\nJones was employed during the\nlast five years in a chief informa\ntion specialist with the department\nof agriculture in Washington. Gar\nrison began his advertising career\nwith the Camphell-Ewald Co,\nlater .joined Jam Handy or\nganization and then became a\nmember of Hcnrv Ford's personal\npublic relations ?laff in 1941.\nHOW EXPERTS PICK DETROIT RACES\nDew Walter Col. Pick* t\u2019nlted Pre\u00bba Trackman Clocker Charlie I. X. 8. Consensua\nProjoe Victory Mac Victory Mac Victory Mac Projor Projoe Projoe\nFIRST RACE Monighan Projoe Projoe Monighan Victory Mae Momghan Victory Mae\nFlaps Hustling Don Agency Hustling Don Monighan Victory Mae Monighan\nGvpsy Actress Gypsy Actress Gypsy Actrea* Gypsy Actress Rreak Thru Gypsy Actress Gypsy Actress\nSECOND RACE Break Thru Break Thru Damien*! Ariel Cat Like Gypsy Actress Rreak Thru Rreak Thru\nDamion s Ariel Cat Like Platinum Sand* Rreak Thru Tctramore _ Cat I. ike ('at Like\nLeaping Moose Chickie DD, Hogan i Ghickie DD. ('hickie D. D. Valve! Heel* Chickit I) D\nTHIRD RACE Velvet Heel* Vel\\rt Heels Kantar Run Velvet Heels Velvet Heels Chickie D. D. Velvet Heels\nChickie DD. Leaping Moose Leaping Moose De